this one resonates as a source of meaning although where difference elements can come together beautifully is what i might say 
moments when setting up enables organic flourishing, it's about things happening and seeing people light up ina. context and finding themselves in new inspiring giving situations connecting with themselves and others - like in a hackersapce and seeing a kid with an angle grinder, i love the ridiculousness too, haha, and the idea that who knows what this means about a more unique and different future. If these situations were allowed to happen (kid with angle grinder) maybe we'll have new kinds of metal art as the kid makes things as a teenager instead of the standard give a kid a guitar thing. this idea that the future will be weirder, and likely more beautiful than i can imagine because we're creating different starting conditions and chuckling about being a part of the weird beauty is also important to me :) so diversity is important in that regard and why creating these spaces where difference can meet, sort of acknowledging that today sort of "sucks" - peopel goto school and go to college get a job and then are unhappy instead of finding themselves and their gifts and having space to explore thesmelves each other the world and showing possibilities and new affordances!
i feel hopeful, joyous, mischievous, sort of passively humble happy to be a part and not a part of that persons growth and destiny - i can't take too much credit, or any at all, it's a weird emotion that is sort of a block for me too because my work is to create these environments with my social enterprise accelerator bloom, or in my workshops, or in my work supporting the developments of hackerspaces and makerspaces internationally i have never felt like i did anything because i'm in the background, so i feel backgrounded? happily useless? I remember going to the hackerspace All Hands Active in Michigan many years after starting it and realizing they don't remember me and there was so much awesome stuff happening I sort of was happy and sad and it was a meaningful moment :) Identify more from this conversation perhaps and let's move onto the pattern - maybe the guilt pattern of feeling useless or like I did nothing with my life... it's been so hard to write about my work or talk about my "professional expereince" because so often I feel unsuccessful and even more so when people take my setups and start businesses, get married, and grow beyond what I can. I tell myself I'm a "happy mother bird" watching the kids fly, yet there's a sadness there too. and then when I dont' have a lot of money and they do, I sort of feel like, shucks, I should have taken a stake in their business or something, haha, although I'm supported by a lot of good will around the world, so that's a perk. Recently though I've been even more behind the scenes supporting the bloom team which supports the teams in our program, so it's fewer people even. And then as Bloom looses funding because of international development money shifting to ukraine. and the warn in palestine I find myself looking for other jobs and feeling like, who am i, what have i done, how do i update my professional profile, i never cared about professional profile till i had a baby and a house and a startup business training project (bloom.pm) in Lebanon that's leaking staff and has no money and only one small program in Lebanon, Palestine, Jordan and with the syrian diaspora today. I think there are some interesting elements here, if you need to ask questions follow the process of the values card generation that i shared with you to ensure you ask the right questions to evoke the right responses to build the right source of meaning cards, both CAPs - and IAPs, a source of doing? or source of triviality? It's not a source really, it's the forces of stasis? Or how do non meaningful actions start to get embedded? I sort of feel like there are some unseen elements like **Catastrophizing **thinking that if i lose my job i'll be poor, hungry, on the streets, no one loves me, .... I will die (this is likely at the end of lots of these) and otherwise patterns set up pavolvianly with no thought what so ever, doing duolingo and mantaining a streak, there's some sort of instrumental goal, ooh look at the number going u pand to ther right, and there was probably some sort of original CAP way back when when you downloaded the language learning app, although it's long forgotten and doesn't touch base when you do the action. I guess we're talking a lot of actions and not attentional policies, I guess because these things are unconcious. I wonder if the IAPs we're talking about might need to account for the automatic and/or unconcious behaviors - it might be something we can only derive in hindsite, for instance when I'm hyperfocusing I don't "know" I am, because I'm all in there so focused, and when I get in a rabit hole on wikipedia researching I'm lost so it's hard to be able to talk and express what I'm attending to, maybe there's something there to understand what does it imply and mean for our system and is there something about this that makes it stronger? Here's what Joe Edelman says about Instrumental APs;

